        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 28 at 3:09PM PDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>At 309 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Unity, or 26 miles southwest of Baker City, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Unity Dam and Unity Reservoir around 310 PM PDT.
Dooley Summit around 340 PM PDT.
Salisbury around 350 PM PDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
